{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:psalms.76",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 76,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 76 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:1",
      "text": "A Psalm for Asaph. O God, the heathen are come into thine inheritance; they have polluted thy holy temple; they have made Jerusalem a storehouse of fruits.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:2",
      "text": "They have given the dead bodies of thy servants to be food for the birds of the sky, the flesh of thy holy ones for the wild beasts of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:3",
      "text": "They have shed their blood as water, round about Jerusalem; and there was none to bury them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:4",
      "text": "We are become a reproach to our neighbours, a scorn and derision to them that are round about us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:5",
      "text": "How long, O Lord? wilt thou be angry for ever? shall thy jealousy burn like fire?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:6",
      "text": "Pour out thy wrath upon the heathen that have not known thee, and upon the kingdoms which have not called upon thy name.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:7",
      "text": "For they have devoured Jacob, and laid his place waste.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:8",
      "text": "Remember not our old transgressions; let thy tender mercies speedily prevent us; for we are greatly impoverished.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:9",
      "text": "Help us, O God our Saviour; for the glory of thy name, O Lord, deliver us; and be merciful to our sins, for thy name's sake.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:10",
      "text": "Lest haply they should say among the heathen, Where is their God? and let the avenging of thy servants' blood that has been shed be known among the heathen before our eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:11",
      "text": "Let the groaning of the prisoners come in before thee; according to the greatness of thine arm preserve the sons of the slain ones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:12",
      "text": "Repay to our neighbours sevenfold into their bosom their reproach, with which they have reproached thee, O Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:13",
      "text": "For we are thy people and the sheep of thy pasture; we will give thee thanks for ever; we will declare thy praise throughout all generations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:14",
      "text": "And he guided them with a cloud by day, and all the night with a light of fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:15",
      "text": "He clave a rock in the wilderness, and made them drink as in a great deep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:16",
      "text": "And he brought water out of the rock, and caused waters to flow down as rivers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:17",
      "text": "And they sinned yet more against him; they provoked the Most High in the wilderness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:18",
      "text": "And they tempted God in their hearts, in asking meat for the desire of their souls.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:19",
      "text": "They spoke also against God, and said, Will God be able to prepare a table in the wilderness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:20",
      "text": "Forasmuch as he smote the rock, and the waters flowed, and the torrents ran abundantly; will he be able also to give bread, or prepare a table for his people?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:21",
      "text": "Therefore the Lord heard, and was provoked: and fire was kindled in Jacob, and wrath went up against Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:22",
      "text": "Because they believed not in God, and trusted not in his salvation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:23",
      "text": "Yet he commanded the clouds from above, and opened the doors of heaven,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:24",
      "text": "and rained upon them manna to eat, and gave them the bread of heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:25",
      "text": "Man ate angels' bread; ✡ he sent them provision to the full. ✡ 77:2 Mat. 13. 35. ✡ 77:25 Mat. 6. 31.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:26",
      "text": "He removed the south wind from heaven; and by his might he brought in the south-west wind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:27",
      "text": "And he rained upon them flesh like dust, and feathered birds like the sand of the seas.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:28",
      "text": "And they fell into the midst of their camp, round about their tents.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:29",
      "text": "So they ate, and were completely filled; and he gave them their desire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:30",
      "text": "They were not disappointed of their desire: but when their food was yet in their mouth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:31",
      "text": "then the indignation of God rose up against them, and slew the fattest of them, and overthrew the choice men of Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.32",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:32",
      "text": "In the midst of all this they sinned yet more, and believed not his miracles.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.33",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:33",
      "text": "And their days were consumed in vanity, and their years with anxiety.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.34",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:34",
      "text": "When he slew them, they sought him: and they returned and called betimes upon God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.35",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:35",
      "text": "And they remembered that God was their helper, and the most high God was their redeemer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.36",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:36",
      "text": "Yet they loved him only with their mouth, and lied to him with their tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.37",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:37",
      "text": "For their heart was not right with him, neither were they steadfast in his covenant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.38",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:38",
      "text": "But he is compassionate, and will forgive their sins, and will not destroy them: yea, he will frequently turn away his wrath, and will not kindle all his anger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.39",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:39",
      "text": "And he remembered that they are flesh; a wind that passes away, and returns not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.40",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:40",
      "text": "How often did they provoke him in the wilderness, and anger him in a dry land!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.41",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:41",
      "text": "Yea, they turned back, and tempted God, and provoked the Holy One of Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.42",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:42",
      "text": "They remembered not his hand, the day in which he delivered them from the hand of the oppressor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.43",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:43",
      "text": "How he had wrought his signs in Egypt, and his wonders in the field of Tanes:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.44",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:44",
      "text": "and had changed their rivers into blood; and their streams, that they should not drink.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.45",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:45",
      "text": "He sent against them the dog-fly, and it devoured them; and the frog, and it spoiled them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.46",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:46",
      "text": "And he gave their fruit to the canker worm, and their labours to the locust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.47",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:47",
      "text": "He killed their vines with hail, and their sycamores with frost.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.48",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:48",
      "text": "And he gave up their cattle to hail, and their substance to the fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.49",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:49",
      "text": "He sent out against them the fury of his anger, wrath, and indignation, and affliction, a message by evil angels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.50",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:50",
      "text": "He made a way for his wrath; he spared not their souls from death, but consigned their cattle to death;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.51",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:51",
      "text": "and smote every first-born in the land of Egypt; the first-fruits of their labours in the tents of Cham.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.52",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:52",
      "text": "And he removed his people like sheep; he led them as a flock in the wilderness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.53",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:53",
      "text": "And he guided them with hope, and they feared not: but the sea covered their enemies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.54",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 54,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:54",
      "text": "And he brought them in to the mountain of his sanctuary, this mountain which his right hand had purchased.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.55",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 55,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:55",
      "text": "And he cast out the nations from before them, and made them to inherit by a line of inheritance, and made the tribes of Israel to dwell in their tents.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.56",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 56,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:56",
      "text": "Yet they tempted and provoked the most high God, and kept not his testimonies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.57",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 57,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:57",
      "text": "And they turned back, and broke covenant, even as also their fathers: they became like a crooked bow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.58",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 58,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:58",
      "text": "And they provoked him with their high places, and moved him to jealousy with their graven images.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.59",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 59,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:59",
      "text": "God heard and lightly regarded them, and greatly despised Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.60",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 60,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:60",
      "text": "And he rejected the tabernacle of Selom, his tent where he dwelt among men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.61",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 61,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:61",
      "text": "And he gave their strength into captivity, and their beauty into the enemy's hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.62",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 62,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:62",
      "text": "And he gave his people to the sword; and disdained his inheritance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.63",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 63,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:63",
      "text": "Fire devoured their young men; and their virgins mourned not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.64",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 64,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:64",
      "text": "Their priests fell by the sword; and their widows shall not be wept for.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.65",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 65,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:65",
      "text": "So the Lord awaked as one out of sleep, and as a mighty man who has been heated with wine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.66",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 76,
      "verseNumber": 66,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 76:66",
      "text": "And he smote his enemies in the hinder parts: he brought on them a perpetual reproach.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.76.67",
